<subSubSection pageId="134" pageNumber="531" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="134.[114,1320,927,1908]" pageId="134" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[117,465,1715,1748]" pageId="134" pageNumber="531">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The [UCN Red List. The Nimba Giant Whitetoothed Shrew is relatively common in secondary habitats, and it probably does not have any major threats, although additional research and assessment are needed.
</paragraph>
